From Robert C Hite Subject Re DAVE KINGMAN FOR THE HALL OF FAME In article Mark Singer writes I'm no Kingman Just thought I'd point out that he's the only player in history to have five three HR Joe Carter has Eddie Murray McCovey and Gehrig also Ruth Mays Foxx and Dawson two Didn't Mike Schmidt also do this at least three times I can remember twice in Wrigley Field did it the same day Kong did it in a shootout and he swatted four there one day in April ' the month he set the April record with HR' Anybody remember any of this I was just a kid